      • DemoCommand

        @AutoGUIAnnotation(DescriptionForUser="<html>Just send something via LAN</html>",
                   ParameterNames={},
                   DefaultValues={},
                   ToolTips={})
 @iC_Annotation(MethodChecksSyntax=false)
public void DemoCommand()
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        throws java.io.IOException
        This is an exemplary implementation of a new device command to help understanding how to write new Instrument Commands. Use the reference implementation to implement new Instrument Commands.

        This method shows a message to the user when in SyntaxCheck mode and also when the 'real' action is performed.

        This method implements the Syntax-Check mode.

        Throws:
        javax.script.ScriptException - when conversion of the Instrument's answer to a float fails.
        java.io.IOException - re-thrown from QueryInstrument
        java.util.zip.DataFormatException - when the Syntax Check failed.
